  "messages": [
    {
      "id": "c68439dd0de632301b73bcdc5b4f03bb752fe8fd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-24 18:57:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThe job of fixing the bad symlinks can be done by e2fsck, since there can be problems trying to do this in the kernel as you have done (doing a write during a read operation can cause problems, or possibly exceed the transaction credits for a nested transaction.\n\nThe main other question I have is why this problem is not hit with normal ext4 filesytems?  That is what makes me think that there is some problem in osd-ldiskfs, or possibly our existing ldiskfs patches. It doesn't seem right that fixing this needs a new ldiskfs patch, since no similar problem is hit with ext4, which is presumably using the same code.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
